AI models and third-party model weights notice

This software uses and/or can use third-party AI models and model weights. The
application code is licensed under MIT as stated above, but each model and
weight file has its own license terms from its original source.

Current model sources used by the desktop app include:

- RetinaFace face detection model (`retinaface_mv2.onnx`):
  https://github.com/yakhyo/retinaface-pytorch/releases/download/v0.0.1/retinaface_mv2.onnx
- ArcFace face embedding model (`w600k_r50.onnx`) mirrors:
  https://huggingface.co/maze/faceX/resolve/main/w600k_r50.onnx
  https://huggingface.co/ll00292007/easyphoto/resolve/main/w600k_r50.onnx
- Nomic embedding models via Transformers.js:
  https://huggingface.co/nomic-ai/nomic-embed-vision-v1.5
  https://huggingface.co/nomic-ai/nomic-embed-text-v1.5

The user is solely responsible for checking and complying with all applicable
licenses, terms, and usage restrictions of those AI models and weights. While
these models are open-source, some model licenses can restrict commercial use
or impose additional obligations depending on distribution and usage scenario.
